HEADWORD: Caryophyllin
<hw>Car`y*oph"yl*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A tasteless and odorless crystalline substance, extracted from
cloves, polymeric with common camphor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caryophyllous</ent>⟦br⟧
